      <h2>UI Patterns</h2>

      <h3>Buttons</h3>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-3);flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;margin:var(--space-4) 0;">
        <a href="#" class="btn" onclick="return false;">Default Button</a>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn--accent" onclick="return false;">Accent Button</a>
      </div>
      <p style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:var(--text-xs);color:var(--color-ink-faint);">Square corners. DM Sans. Uppercase is optional. Border on default, filled on hover.</p>

      <h3>Cards</h3>
      <p>Content cards use <code>background: var(--color-bg-alt)</code> with a <code>1px solid var(--color-rule)</code> border. Article-style cards get a left accent border (3px). Hover lifts with shadow.</p>

      <h3>Section badges</h3>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-2);flex-wrap:wrap;margin:var(--space-4) 0;">
        <span style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;padding:var(--space-1) var(--space-3);background:var(--color-news);color:#fff;">News</span>
        <span style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;padding:var(--space-1) var(--space-3);background:var(--color-opinion);color:#fff;">Opinion</span>
        <span style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;padding:var(--space-1) var(--space-3);background:var(--color-analysis);color:#fff;">Analysis</span>
        <span style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;padding:var(--space-1) var(--space-3);background:var(--color-history);color:#fff;">History</span>
      </div>

      <h3>Spacing</h3>
      <p>All spacing uses a consistent scale from <code>--space-1</code> (0.25rem) to <code>--space-20</code> (5rem). No magic numbers.</p>

      <h3>Border radius</h3>
      <p>Default to <strong>square corners</strong> (<code>border-radius: 0</code>) for a professional, authoritative feel. Rounded corners used only where softness is intentional (pills, toggles).</p>

      <h2>Naming</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Publication name: <strong>The Freethinking Times</strong> (always full, always capitalised)</li>
        <li>Never abbreviated to "TFT" in reader-facing copy</li>
        <li>Prefix for localStorage keys: <code>tft</code></li>
        <li>CSS class convention: BEM-style (<code>.block__element--modifier</code>)</li>
        <li>Design tokens live in <code>tokens.css</code> — edit once, retheme everywhere</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
